      • getPropertyValue

        java.lang.Object getPropertyValue​(java.lang.String propertyName,
                                  java.lang.Object value)
        Returns an appropriate representation of the property with the given name. In most cases, this representation is a simple String that will be added directly to the table on export. In some cases however, such as CReal's units display, the returned value must use one of the data type extensions of AbstractComplexContent.

        This base implementation handles properties of type AbstractCReal and String.

        NOTE: null should be returned for properties that should not be displayed.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - a String containing the property name retrieved via this component's BeanInfo with a Property Set.
        value - the current value of the given property
        Returns:
        an Object that will be used to create text appropriate for display in the properties tables exported for this component or null if the property should be ignored.

      • getPropertyValue

        java.lang.Object getPropertyValue​(java.beans.PropertyDescriptor descriptor,
                                  java.lang.Object value)
        Returns an appropriate representation of the property using the given property descriptor. In most cases, this representation is a simple String that will be added directly to the table on export. In some cases however, such as CReal's units display, the returned value must use one of the data type extensions of AbstractComplexContent.

        This method calls getPropertyValue(java.lang.String, java.lang.Object) for anything except Boolean and Integer values that have no property exitor defined.

        NOTE: null should be returned for properties that should not be displayed.

        Parameters:
        descriptor - the PropertyDescriptor that describes the property that the given value corresponds to.
        value - the current value of the given property
        Returns:
        an Object that will be used to create text appropriate for display in the properties tables exported for this component or null if the property should be ignored.
